entry.title: [chromedriver] Ignore nonexistent windows in `window/handles`
entry.content:
`chromedriver` implements webdriver classic's "Get Window Handles"

endpoint [0] using CDP's `Target.getTargets`, followed by enumerating

new web views with `Target.attachToTarget` [1, 2].



However, a browsing context returned from `getTargets` may `close()`

itself [3] before `chromedriver` attaches to it, which returns "no such

window" to the `chromedriver` client (contrary to the spec). In this CL,

assume "newly created" windows may not exist because of this race and

simply don't process them.



[0]: https://www.w3.org/TR/webdriver2/#get-window-handles

[1]: https://chromedevtools.github.io/devtools-protocol/tot/Target/

[2]: https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/main:chrome/test/chromedriver/chrome/chrome_impl.cc;l=125-126;drc=8e78783dc1f7007bad46d657c9f332614e240fd8;bpv=0;bpt=1

[3]: https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/main:third_party/blink/web_tests/external/wpt/html/anonymous-iframe/resources/embedding-test.js;l=37-39;drc=6445759719756538840d3af83fc798daeec4995e;bpv=0;bpt=0



Bug: 1506833

Change-Id: Ia1f344eb0d991835c118cb4591fb90ad580d76e0

Cq-Include-Trybots: luci.chromium.try:linux-blink-rel

Test: PS1 reliably reproduced the race; goes away with the fix.

entry.title: Generate OffsetMapping correctly for variable-length `text-transform`
entry.content:
`text-transform` can change the text length, but OffsetMappingBuilder

and InlineItemsBuilder didn't support such cases. This CL fixes it.



* TransformedString keeps track of such length changes.

It's converted from WTF::TextOffsetMap



* InlineItemsBuilder sets up TransformedString with such data, and

use the data to call appropriate OffsetMappingBuilder::

Append*Mapping().



* ComputedStyle: Add WTF::TextOffsetMap argument to ApplyTextTransform()



* LayoutText: Add HasVariableLengthTransform flag.



Bug: 486880, 750990

entry.title: Reland: [BRP] Remove ref-count-size experiment parameter
entry.content:
[Same as crrev.com/c/5149451 but w/o fieldtrial_testing_config.json]



Assume everywhere that 0 was passed, which means "use natural size".

This means use sizeof(PartitionRefCount), possibly adjusted to

workaround certain issues:

1) MTE/BRP race (crbug.com/1445816)

2) Mac 13 & 14 crashes (crbug.com/1378822, crbug.com/1457756)

But this calculation happens internally and is unaffected by this CL.

The only difference is that we can no longer externally override

ref_count_size to something higher.



This CL is considered a no-op, since the default param size is

"natural" (i.e. 0).
